HEADWORD: Compeer
<hw>Com*peer"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <ety>[OE. <ets>comper</ets>, through
French fr. L. <ets>compar</ets>; <ets>com-</ets> + <ets>par</ets> equal.
See <er>Peer</er> an equal, and cf. 1st <er>Compare</er>.]</ety> <def>An
equal, as in rank, age, prowess, etc.; a companion; a comrade; a
mate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And him thus answer'd soon his bold <qex>compeer</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His <qex>compeer</qex> in arms.</q> <rj><qau>Ford.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

